Sep 6 2009 	Surprisingly nice--much better than we expected	This is now called the CitiGarden, and it's set back from the street behind a huge parking lot and it looks like an office complex--from the outside it doesn't look at all inspiring for a hotel, and in fact it's easy to miss it if you're not looking carefully. I don't think it had a street-side sign. However, when we got in, it's a different story. The photos on their website are correct, but the rooms are much nicer in person. It looks like they are renovating the whole place, by degrees. We stayed in a room which had already been re-done, but there was a whole section of rooms which were being painted &amp; renovated while we were there. I loved the bathroom part of our room--the sink was very stylish, sort of a slab of granite on top of kind of wooden furniture legs. It had a large framed mirror above the sink and nice chrome fixtures and lights above the mirror. It just looked really upscale, and much better than I expected for an airport motel. All the wood in the room was a dark mahogany finish. There was good closet space next to the sink and the shower was good as well. There was a little heater under the window (which we made use of!). The bedroom did have a strange sickly shade of green on one wall. I don't know who thought that was a good idea. Maybe it looked better on the swatch. But overall, the room is nicer than the photo shows.The hotel has a tiny gym as well, but it is tiny, just a few machines and some weights. If you're a fitness fanatic, you'll be disappointed.It was far too cold to brave the pool (when would it EVER be warm enough for that??) which was not heated.The breakfast buffet was pretty disappointing--some cereal, toast, OJ and coffee as far as I remember. But most motels don't even do breakfast anyway, so I guess it's an improvement on that.We didn't try the Chinese buffet restaurant adjacent to it, but we found out afterwards that it's pretty popular. Instead we went up to the main street of South San Francisco, which is very cute, and has lots of restaurants, etc. The location of the hotel is very convenient for the airport, and their free shuttle apparently runs every half an hour (it is a shared shuttle service with some other hotels--we had to look closely at every shuttle for their name).I hope the maids do their job properly, or it will start to go downhill. The beautiful chrome taps were already scratched (they obviously just used scrubby sponges on them, which is a no-no!), two of our lights weren't working (we complained to reception and they sent someone right away) and there were dead bugs trapped in the light fixture above the sink--nobody's fault, this happens, but someone has to notice it and do something about it.Overall, for the price, location, and the place itself, we'd be happy to stay there again. I just hope they keep it nice.	
